  "response_text": "The quadratic formula is derived from the general form of a quadratic equation, which is:\n\nax^2 + bx + c = 0\n\nTo derive the quadratic formula, we start by rearranging the equation to isolate the x^2 term:\n\nax^2 + bx = -c\n\nNext, we add (b/2a)^2 to both sides of the equation to complete the square:\n\nax^2 + bx + (b/2a)^2 = -c + (b/2a)^2\n\nThis can be rewritten as:\n\na(x^2 + (b/a)x + (b/2a)^2) = -c + (b/2a)^2\n\nNow, we can factor the left-hand side of the equation as a perfect square:\n\na(x + b/2a)^2 = -c + (b/2a)^2\n\nNext, we can divide both sides of the equation by a:\n\n(x + b/2a)^2",
